<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-15T10:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-15T10:36:00-05:00" n="250" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.111/3588</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-15T10:00:00-05:36">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Joaquin Tinoco has requested me to ask if there is any objection to
                                his going early in April to France via the United States. He says
                                that if there is no objection, he is going to join French Army at
                                the front through the medium of Costa Rican Minister at Paris. Doubt
                                sincerity of his intention to leave, but if he goes, retirement of
                                Tinoco will be easier of accomplishment.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>